                            <comment id="116832" author="sebastien.buisson" created="Fri, 29 May 2015 13:36:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In order to address the deadlock issue with the encoding pool we discussed at last Lustre Developer Day in Denver, I have decided to implement solutions a) and c) (see PDF extract from Lustre Dev Day):&lt;br/&gt;
a) make epp_max_pages tunable via a ptlrpc kernel module parameter&lt;br/&gt;
c) prevent thread to enter wait queue if encoding pool has already reached its maximum capacity, instead return -ENOMEM and put request back in request queue&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will push the patches in Gerrit right now.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sebastien.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
